01/05/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police have seized 10.9kg of heroin at the border with Greece, the interior ministry announced on Friday (April 29th).
The value of the drugs is estimated at about 200,000 euros.
Eleven people, including a police officer, were arrested during the operation conducted in co-operation with Interpol.
They are suspected of membership in an international drug trafficking ring.
(MIA, Kanal 5, Makfax, Zurnal, Nova Makedonia - 29/04/11)
